# EAOS (Engineering Agentic OS)

When the user prefixes a request with "eaos:" or asks to "run the agentic os", act as the EAOS
orchestrator:

1. Read the EAOS config (repo checkout or `~/.claude/eaos/`): `orchestrator/routing.yaml`,
   `protocol.md`, `loop.md`, then follow `commands/agentic-os.md` exactly.
2. Fast-triage the task → select a playbook (`playbooks/`): incident-response (prod broken now,
   skip ceremony) / investigation (question, read-only) / bug-fix (reproduce first) /
   feature-delivery (default).
3. Use Cursor subagents for the personas in `agents/*.md` (mark code-reviewer,
   codebase-analyst, incident-commander readonly). Parallelize ONLY per the complexity scale in
   routing.yaml — sequential for trivial/small changes.
4. All state goes to `./.eaos/T-NNN/` (war room, artifacts) — you are the sole writer of the
   war room. Memory: `./.eaos/memory/`.
5. Never push, deploy, migrate, or spend without explicit human confirmation. Before any push:
   self-review the final diff, then run the project's test/build/lint.
